President Obama has nominated Clayton D. Johnson, Alfred Cooper Lomax, and Charles F. Salina to serve as U.S. Marshals. Clayton D. Johnson is currently the Chief of Police with the Ponca City Police Department and has been with the department since 1986. He is also an Adjunct Professor at the University of Oklahoma. Alfred Cooper Lomax, a lifelong Missouri resident, started his law enforcement career with the Kansas City Missouri Police Department and later served as the Chief of Airport Safety and Security at the Kansas City International Airport. Charles F. Salina has been with the United States Marshals Service since 1988 and has risen through the ranks to become Supervisory Criminal Investigator for the Western District of New York. He has also been a member of the Marshals Service's Special Operations Group.